{
  "stem": "3928.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So what happened is this, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had a coat, an overcoat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I exchanged an overcoat for a passport of a woman.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they doctored up the picture, almost like looked like me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And because when we go from there to Salzburg, they had to go through a Russian checkpoint, because there from the Russian zone, you went to them on the-- the American zone.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Salzburg was an American zone.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So in order to buy this, I gave up my coat, in December, to get over to Salzburg.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from Salzburg, again, for the last money I had, I gave for a guy to took me over to Germany, to the German and the Austrian border.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I ended up in Bamberg, Germany, and I-- as a refugee, as a Hungarian refugee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I find a job with the United Nations Children's service, UNESCO.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I work with the-- their job was, at the time, was different like today.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Their job was to reunite children with parents who were lost.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I worked with an English lady, by the name of Huxley.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Agnes Huxley was her name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I worked with her and until I came to the United States in 1951.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I came to Buda-- to-- to Pittsburgh.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I received a scholarship to the University of Pittsburgh.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I-- my first job was as I-- part of my-- my study was I had to work on the educational station for credit.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And a first job was I worked with Fred Rogers, on which, at the time, they called And at the time, there was only two television stations in Pittsburgh.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One was KDKA, which at the time called WDTV-TV, and channel 13, WQED.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
